%% Diagram: Trace ID propagation across services
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Client
    participant Edge as API Gateway
    participant Auth as Auth Service
    participant Pay as Payment Service
    participant Notif as Notification Service
    participant Logs as Log Pipeline

    Client->>Edge: POST /checkout
    Edge->>Edge: generate trace_id=abc123
    Edge-->>Logs: log {trace_id: abc123, svc: edge}
    Edge->>Auth: GET /verify (X-Request-ID: abc123)
    Auth-->>Logs: log {trace_id: abc123, svc: auth}
    Auth-->>Edge: 200 OK
    Edge->>Pay: POST /charge (X-Request-ID: abc123)
    Pay-->>Logs: log {trace_id: abc123, svc: payment}
    Pay-->>Edge: 200 OK
    Edge->>Notif: POST /notify (X-Request-ID: abc123)
    Notif-->>Logs: log {trace_id: abc123, svc: notif}
    Notif-->>Edge: 202 Accepted
    Edge-->>Client: 200 OK

    Note over Logs: Query: {trace_id="abc123"}\nReconstructs full request path
